<P>
   MONTINI-COLUMN (Phoenix) Alfredo Rivas read the entire parental
contract, even the fine print, and when he awoke to a raging fire
and screaming from the bedroom of his children, he honored it. He
went in after them. I was beginning to wonder if there were any
parents like this left in the world. There are. By E. J. Montini.
