 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE COMMENTARY BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These columns for release Wednesday, August 23, 2000 are moving
today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ If Bill Clinton is indicted and faces potential
prison time after he leaves the presidency for lying under oath
about going too far with Monica Lewinsky, so be it. After all, the
president got himself into this fix and there is no reason why an
ex-president should be cut any legal slack the rest of us wouldn't
get. And that is precisely why Clinton shouldn't be charged. Almost
no one else would be in the same circumstances.(Teepen, Cox News
Service.) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ Howard Kleinberg's column is not available
today. (Kleinberg, Cox News Service.)
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ With summer's end, the pace in Pelee Island,
Ontario slackens as ferries from the Canadian and U.S. mainlands
cut back their shuttles to a sparse winter schedule that lasts
until the lake freezes over. Life on the island slows to a pleasant
walk. I know because I've been reading all about it in some back
issues of the local newspaper - The Grapevine. (Schuett, Cox News
Service) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   BOOKMAN-COLUMN _ While the GOP may officially oppose what it
calls ``quotas,'' there's no question that party leaders wanted a
certain number of minority faces broadcast on the nation's TV
screens from the convention in Philadelphia, and that those faces
were far out of proportion to their actual number and influence in
the party. Rather than an expression of hypocrisy, however, perhaps
it's best to look at that radiant picture of diversity from
Philadelphia as the stating of a goal. (Bookman, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ The arrival of another school year brings to mind
contraband. Not drugs, but the more benign goods of another time.
(Young, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   JOEMURRAY-COLUMN _ An eye problem keeps columnist Joe Murray
home from the Democratic convention and reminds him of a childhood
game with cousin Bubba. (Joe Murray, Cox News Service). MOVED.
</P>
