   INDIANS-POLITICS (Lummi Reservation, Wash.) _ In this far corner
of Indian country, people see two Slade Gortons, the senator who
helped to secure funds for tribal projects and the man who has
spent much of his public life battling the Lummis and other tribes
on everything from fishing rights to the power of governing their
own affairs. Gorton has feuded with American Indians but has never
suffered a strong political backlash from the tribes. But this
year, flush with money from casino gambling operations, Indians
across the country say they are going to make him pay. By Timothy
Egan.
</P>
