<SLUG> BC-ADVISORY-NNS </SLUG>
  
 (ATTENTION EDITORS: This advisory describes the top offerings from
Newhouse News Service for TUESDAY, AUGUST 22. For information about
purchasing articles as a ``separate-buy,'' contact Debra Weydert of
the New York Times Syndicate at 1-732-390-4480; fax, 732-390-4697;
e-mail: weyded(at)nytimes.com.)
<TEXT>
<P>
   FALLEN-IDOLS _ It's been an off-season of discontent for the
National Football League, with several players accused of felonies
in high-profile criminal cases. It'a PR problem for the league, but
what about the impression on young fans vulnerable to
around-the-clock media hype of football players marketed as mythic
figures? Photos. About 2,300
</P>
<P>
   CAMPAIGN-MILITARY _ Presidential candidates George W. Bush and
Al Gore are trading glib boasts about how they will beef up U.S.
military power, find a clear strategy and fix readiness problems.
But Pentagon analysts and savvy outsiders dismiss much of this as
political blather. About 1,000
</P>
<P>
   NO-SURVIVOR _ Even before the final episode airs Wednesday, fans
of the reality TV show ``Survivor'' are in mourning. Just why has
this show been so habit forming? As one fan says, ``It's sort of
like watching a car wreck ... you know it's wrong to stare but you
just can't help yourself.'' About 900
</P>
</TEXT>
