SAN FRANCISCO _  ROVING FEAST  _ Editor's note: Today we begin
``The Roving Feast'' by Marlena Spieler, a frequent contributor to
the Food Section for nearly 12 years. In her column, which will run
every other week, Marlena will lead us through her special world of
food locally and abroad. &HT;     By Marlena Spieler  
 c. 2000 The San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
SAN FRANCISCO _  &UR; FEAST-PESTO &LR;  _ I have a pair of stylish sunglasses
I bought in San Francisco last spring. I managed to pull them out
for a sultry couple of days in Portofino but they've been lying
around since then.
<P>
   We were in Liguria taping material about pesto for the British
Broadcasting Co. when we got an invitation we couldn't refuse:
Would we like to stay a night at the Hotel Splendido?
</P>
<P>
   Main story with sidebar and recipes. &QL; 
 &UR; By Marlena Spieler &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; c. 2000 The San Francisco Chronicle &QL;  &LR; 
