<P>
   RETIRED-WRITERS (Undated) _ The retiring literary set is a group
usually overlooked in all the attention attracted by an elder
writer like Saul Bellow, who this year, at 85, delivered his first
major novel in more than a decade, ``Ravelstein.'' The very notion
of a pension is not a theme suitable for publishing party
conversation. The issue is so sensitive that some writers simply
refuse to discuss it. By Doreen Carvajal.
</P>
<P>
   GREAT-ACTORS (Undated) _ Critic's Notebook: Who was the greatest
actor of them all? By Mel Gussow.
</P>
<P>
   SHARK-BOOK-REVIEW (Undated) _ On ``The Shark Net,'' Robert
Drewe's spiced and savory memoir of his boyhood years in Perth,
Australia, when the rampages of a serial killer mingled with the
more normal events of a young life, making them all seem like
threads of the same tableau. Reviewed by Richard Bernstein.
</P>
<P>
   TV-NOTES (Undated) _ News and notes on television. By Jim
Rutenberg.
