 Attn Sports Editors:  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Sports stories from The New York Times News Service for
 &UR; WEDNESDAY &LR; , Aug. 23.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-VECSEY-COLUMN (New York) _ Sports of The Times column on
Patrick Ewing. By George Vecsey.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-KNICKS-TRADE (New York) _ The Knicks resume efforts to
complete a deal that will end Patrick Ewing's 15-year tenure in New
York. By Mike Wise.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-YANKS-RANGERS (New York) _ Texas at the Yankees, 7:05 p.m.
EDT start. By Buster Olney.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-METS-PADRES (San Diego) _ N.Y. Mets at San Diego, 5:05 p.m.
EDT start. By Tyler Kepner.
</P>
<P>
   OLY-ARBITRATION _ There's a new Olympic sport this year:
arbitration. The two latest examples are a Greco-Roman wrestler
named Sieracki and a cyclist named Chris Witty who were selected
for their respective teams, only to have a disappointed competitor
challenge their selection. Neither athlete was informed that his
case had gone to arbitration, nor invited to appear before the
arbitrator. By Jere Longman.
</P>
<P>
   For information and repeats call the News Service at (888)
346-9867 or (212) 556-1927. And be sure to look for other sports
stories from our partners: The Boston Globe, Cox News Service,
Hearst News Service, The Arizona Republic, Kansas City Star, Fort
Worth Star-Telegram, Los Angeles Daily News, San Francisco
Chronicle and Seattle Post-Intelligencer.
</P>
