<P>
   RETIRED-WRITERS (Undated) _ The retiring literary set is a group
usually overlooked in all the attention attracted by an elder
writer like Saul Bellow, who this year, at 85, delivered his first
major novel in more than a decade, ``Ravelstein.'' The very notion
of a pension is not a theme suitable for publishing party
conversation. The issue is so sensitive that some writers simply
refuse to discuss it. By Doreen Carvajal.
</P>
