have a powerful influence on other types of behavior.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's that thing called celebrity fame,'' Green said. ``I'm not
exploiting it from the standpoint of making dollars. But I'm
exploiting it from the standpoint of trying to access the hearts
and minds of youths and trying to turn them toward what is right,
what is honest and what is respectable.''
</P>
<P>
   (SECOND OPTIONAL TRIM BEGINS) \roMDUL\ &UR; - But for every moment of
attention from a Darrell Green, there seems to be a counter-moment
from a Plaxico Burress, first-round draft pick of the Pittsburgh
Steelers, which gave him a $5.5 million signing bonus.
</P>
