<HEADER>
A9172 &Cx1f; tad-z
r a BC-BILINGUAL-BOX-$ADV27-     08-22 0370
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BILINGUAL-BOX-$ADV27-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    With BILINGUAL-AMERICA. For release Sunday, Aug. 27.
 &HT;    c.2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Over the past decade, the United States has experienced its
largest wave of immigration since early in the 20th century. The
surge has presented American businesses with a huge new pool of
workers and new opportunities to market products to a growing
consumer class. But language and cultural barriers have caused
workplace battles.
</P>
<P>
   DISCRIMINATION LAWSUITS ON THE RISE
</P>
<P>
   The U.S. Equal Employment Opportunity Commission has filed an
increasing number of charges against companies alleging that they
fired or forced the resignation of workers by enacting ``English
only'' policies on the job.
</P>
<P>
   1996: 77
</P>
<P>
   1997: 142
</P>
<P>
   1998: 150
</P>
<P>
   1999: 253
</P>
<P>
   Source: EEOC
</P>
<P>
   MINORITY SPENDING POWER CLIMBING FAST
</P>
<P>
   The spending power of the two largest immigrant groups,
Hispanics and Asian-Americans, are expanding faster than the
general population.
</P>
<P>
   .............................Total
U.S.............................Asian-
</P>
<P>
   .................................(billions)
</P>
<P>
   1990......................$4.2...............$207.9...........$113.1
</P>
<P>
   1995......................$5.3...............$289.4...........$167.2
</P>
<P>
   1996......................$5.6...............$304.4...........$179.3
</P>
<P>
   1997......................$5.9...............$327.7...........$193.7
</P>
<P>
   1998......................$6.2...............$354.0...........$210.0
</P>
<P>
   1999......................$6.9...............$383.3...........$228.6
</P>
<P>
   Change, 1990-99.....56.7%.............84.4%...........102.2%
</P>
<P>
   Source: University of Georgia's Selig Center for Economic Growth
</P>
