Texas universities for minority students, Gov. George W. Bush
signed a law in 1997 that guaranteed a spot for any Texan who
graduated in the top 10 percent of their high school class. But
other states are rejecting the rule as short-sighted. By Patrick
Healy. 1300 words. (p and a coding) GRAPHIC: 11 picas x 4 inches,
``Longhorn diversity.''
