<P>
   MICROSOFT-ANTITRUST (Undated) _ Microsoft files a legal brief
with the Supreme Court asking that a lower court review its
antitrust appeal. The brief is in response to arguments the
government made on Aug. 15, requesting that the Supreme Court hear
the company's appeal quickly so ``that justice is not denied
through delay.'' By Steve Lohr.
</P>
<P>
   from the MANAGEMENT PAGE
</P>
<P>
   HUDSON-BRADY (Undated) _ The Boss column: Katherine M. Hudson,
chief executive of the Brady Corp., a manufacturer of
identification and material-solution products
</P>
<P>
   EXTREME-TELECOMMUTERS (Undated) _ Extreme telecommuters describe
people who hold down full-time salaried positions, complete with
benefits, and yet are no ordinary 9-to-5, cubicle-inhabiting
drones. The goal of an extreme telecommuter is to happily blur the
line between working and having an adventure, whether it is touring
Europe, scaling a mountain or pedaling a bike across the United
States. Such telecommuters are rare, of course. Still, some experts
suspect that the ranks of extreme telecommuters may slowly swell
over the next few years, especially if the labor market remains
tight and wireless technology continue to expand. By Sana Siwolop.
</P>
