<P>
   LINCOLN-AD-COLUMN (New York) _ While there are plenty of
sponsors at the U.S. Open tennis tournament, which begins on
Monday, one sponsor intends to stand out _ quite literally _ among
visitors to Flushing Meadows, in Queens County, N.Y., where the
event is held. Starting on Sept. 1, Lincoln Mercury, the Ford Motor
unit based in Irvine, Calif., will usher visitors through
elaborately staged exhibits in a pavilion the size of four tennis
courts to promote a more contemporary image. In creating the
unusual exhibits, Lincoln is embracing a new idea in marketing
called experience marketing. It tries to appeal to consumers
through the senses, often through show business-like techniques. By
