<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR TUESDAY, AUG. 22 
</HEADLINE>
  (EDS: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday, Aug. 23. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-RUSSIA-FATE-NYT (moved on Monday, August 21) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, August 21,
about Russian officials' suspicions that the submarine Kursk sank
after a collision, probably with a foreign submarine, referred
incorrectly to a comment by Russia's defense minister, Marshal Igor
D. Sergeyev, about a buoy observed at the site. He said Russian
lookouts had seen a signal buoy of the type used by Western fleets
to send emergency messages to their bases. He did not say the Kursk
had shot a buoy to the surface to warn that it was in trouble.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BC-YOUTHS-EXECUTE-NYT (moved on Monday, August 21) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, August 21,
about death row inmates who were minors when they committed their
crimes misstated the given name of a South Carolina district
attorney who defended the execution of such prisoners. He is Walter
Bailey, not Wayne.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BC-NY-HUDSON-NYT (moved on Sunday, August 20) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, August 20,
about the growth of tourism in the Hudson Valley misstated Gov.
George E. Pataki's position on industrial development there. While
he has pushed to build industrial plants in the Hudson Valley, he
has not advocated building power plants there.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BC-NY-DUCASSE-NYT (moved on Tuesday, July 11) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, July 11,
about the new Alain Ducasse restaurant in New York and an editorial
about it on Aug. 4 misstated the number of waiters on its staff. A
letter from the restaurant dated Aug. 15 points out that it has 15
waiters; 55 is the total number of employees.  &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
