<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Ramseys to be interviewed by Colorado police next week
 &HT;    By Craig Schneider
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA - John and Patsy Ramsey will sit for further questioning
from Boulder, Colo., investigators on Monday in Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   The first police interviews with the Ramseys in more than two
years will focus on new questions that have emerged regarding the
1996 slaying of their daughter, JonBenet, said Boulder Police Chief
Mark Beckner.
</P>
<P>
   He declined to discuss those questions.
</P>
<P>
   ``We would like to get some answers to some things we're not
sure of,'' said Beckner, who will be part of a seven-member
investigative team that conducts the videotaped interviews.
</P>
<P>
   The Ramseys' attorney, Lin Wood of Atlanta, said the couple
hopes the interviews will help the police solve the murder. They
also want the police to eventually clear their name of any
suspicion, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Neither side anticipates the interviews, expected to take a day
or two, will end with a quick arrest or an immediate statement from
police clearing the couple of suspicion.
</P>
<P>
   As for clearing the Ramseys in the future, Beckner said, ``If we
are able to prove somebody else did it, then that's a possibility.
I don't know how else we could do that with certainty.''
</P>
